FBIS3-59888 "jptac001___94013" JPRS-TAC-94-001 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Arms Control 18 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS Tripartite Efforts on Nuclear Issue By U.S., Ukraine, Russia Kravchuk Predicts Nuclear Accord LD2212092093 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0600 GMT 22 Dec 93 LD2212092093 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] The United States, Russia, and Ukraine will sign a tripartite agreement with regard to compensating Ukraine for the removal of its nuclear weapons and also security guarantees. This has been announced to journalists in Kiev by Ukraine President Leonid Kravchuk. In his words, reports Interfax, this will be an agreement which will not affect the interests of any state. He also confirmed that 17 SS-24 missiles have been stood down from combat duty. The president said that they cannot be used, even by Russia.
